Australia Newcastle Thermal Coal Rises 0.5% to $123.89 a Ton

-- B y   R a j e s h   K u m a r   S i n g h
-- 
2011-03-25T12:22:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/australia-newcastle-thermal-coal-rises-0-5-to-123-89-a-ton.html
Power-station coal  prices  at
 Australia ’s Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, rose 0.5 percent
in the week ending today.  Coal prices at the New South Wales port increased to
$123.89 a metric ton from $123.29 the previous week, according
to the  globalCOAL NEWC Index .  Xstrata Plc (XTA) , the world’s largest exporter of power-station
coal,  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  and Rio Tinto Group are among mining
companies that ship coal through Newcastle.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rajesh Kumar Singh in Delhi at 
 rsingh133@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amit Prakash at   aprakash1@bloomberg.net . 